Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of recognizing if a given graph is the square of a split graph, with a focus on split graphs that are 3-sun-free. This problem falls under the category of graph theory and combinatorics, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories, as they cover topics related to graph theory and combinatorics. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category, as it deals with algorithms and data structures for geometric problems, which can be applied to graph problems. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are less likely categories, but still relevant as they cover topics related to graph algorithms and computational complexity.
